adjectives.description: penetrable (comparative more penetrable, superlative most penetrable)

entries.meaning: Capable of being penetrated, entered, or pierced. Also figuratively.
examples: On the east the high mountain-chain of Zagros, penetrable only in one or two places, forms a barrier of the most marked character, and is beyond a doubt the natural limit for which we are looking.
